Implied Volatility Analytics Dashboard
Built with Python, Power Query, Streamlit & iVolatility API
Project Overview

This is a dynamic Implied Volatility (IV) analytics application designed to help traders analyze options volatility behavior, identify trading opportunities, and monitor volatility trends across multiple symbols.

The system automatically fetches raw options data via the iVolatility API, processes it using Python and Power Query, and presents interactive analytics through a professional Streamlit dashboard.

The application is structured for daily end-of-day (EOD) analysis and supports multi-symbol dynamic screening.

Key Features
1. Real-Time IV Data Integration

Automated data fetching using iVolatility API
Daily EOD data updates
Multi-symbol dynamic loading
Structured CSV-based historical storage

2. Volatility Analytics Engine
ATM Implied Volatility tracking
IV term structure analysis
IV expansion and contraction detection
Volatility regime identification

3. Screening Capability
Dynamic symbol selection
High IV and Low IV opportunity filters

4. Interactive Dashboard 
Clean, professional interface
Expandable and interactive charts
Symbol-wise filtering
Timeframe selection
Comparative analytics



